<item>
            <title>[JDK-8301248] Less side effects in InstanceRefKlass::trace_reference_gc</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8301248</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>The InstanceRefKlass::trace_reference_gc function is called when using oop_iterate on a reference object. Since oop_iterate is a general iterator that can be used for anything, including verification code, it would be desirable for this code to not have subtle side effects. We currently apply load barriers which &amp;quot;fix&amp;quot; pointers in the heap. As a result, verification code that was meant to detect bugs, can end up fixing and hiding the bug. This CR aims to address this.</description>
